l-backups-video/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&#8594;</span></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-launch-new-how-to-use-incremental-backups-video/\">New &#8216;How to use incremental backups&#8217; video released</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"wmullins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1670:\"<p>If you are thinking of backing up your WordPress site content, such as images, media, video, plugins and themes by using UpdraftPlus&#8217; <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-launch-revoluntionary-new-incremental-backups-feature/\">incremental backup</a> feature, you may be interested in our new &#8216;How to use incremental backups&#8217; instructional video.</p>\n<p>While we have existing in-depth <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-use-incremental-backups/\">written instructions</a> on how to use incremental backups, we understand that some people may prefer the quick, visual method of learning and instruction that a video gives. We are always happy to provide our users with different options and hope that the new instructional video provides additional support.</p>\n<p>The video goes through the process of showing you how to take a one-off incremental backup and also how to schedule and setup your incremental backups.</p>\n<p>Check out the video below and be sure to let us know what you think in the comment section.</p>\n<p><iframe src=\"https://playe